WorldStage NewsOnline—-As the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) prepares for Saturday’s supplementary poll in Adamawa, Benue and Sokoto states, the Federal Government has ordered the closure of land borders in affected states ahead of the election. Minister of Interior, retired Lt.-Gen. Abdulrahman Dambazau made the disclosure in a statement signed by Comptroller-General, Nigeria Immigration Service, Mr Muhammad Babandede, in Abuja on Thursday. According to him, the closure of the borders is with effect from Friday noon to Sunday noon. He said the aim is to restrict movements across the borders of the affected states during the election. “The public is to take note and ensure compliance,” he said.